OL,3,CWhat do new official figures tell us
OL,4,Cabout UK job market?
OL,6,FJob vacancies in Britain have dropped
OL,7,Fto their lowest level in five years,
OL,8,Fnew data has shown.
OL,10,FThe number of open positions dropped
OL,11,Fto 705,000 between February and April,
OL,12,Fthe lowest number since the same
OL,13,Fperiod in 2021 - when some Covid
OL,14,Frestrictions were still in place, the
OL,15,FOffice for National Statistics (ONS)
OL,16,Fsaid on Tuesday.
OL,18,FRetail and hospitality jobs have been
OL,19,Fparticularly hard hit, with "economic
OL,20,Fand geopolitical uncertainty" cited as
OL,21,Fa reason behind the drop in hiring.
